Calling resolveTypeName(typeName) here before DcaeServiceTypesQueryStatement.create() will cause typeName wild card match using * to fail. 
For example when a query against "/dcae-service-types?typeName=somepartialtypename*" will not match/work.
I suggest moving this if (typeName != null) block with resolveTypeName() method to DcaeServiceTypeObjectRepository class right before line: 
ifNotNullBind(typeName, it -> query.bind("typeName", it));

So updated DcaeServiceTypeObjectRepository would look like (1st and last lines are existing/unchanged):

Query<DCAEServiceTypeObject> query = getQuery(jdbiHandle, queryStatement);

if (typeName != null){
   typeName = resolveTypeName(typeName);
}

ifNotNullBind(typeName, it -> query.bind("typeName", it));


Will also need to update: DcaeServiceTypesApiServiceImplTests.java to replace:

DcaeServiceTypesApiServiceImpl.resolveTypeName

with:

DcaeServiceTypeObjectRepository.resolveTypeName

but typeName is used in line 122 and 172. When I move this section to DcaeServiceTypeObjectRepository then it will break the logic.

How this could break functionality? I resolving type name before fetching data from repository only when type name is not null. resolveTypeName changes * to % character. Original behavior of dcaeServiceTypesGet was not changed.

    static String resolveTypeName(String typeName){
        if (typeName.contains("*")) {
            return typeName.replaceAll("\\*", "%");
        }
        return typeName;
    }
